items.definition: The Northern Territory University was established in January 1989, after an amalgamation took place between the Darwin Institute of Technology and the University College of the Northern Territory. In 2004 the Northern Territory University merged with the Alice Springs' Centralian College to form the Charles Darwin University. (Courtesy of Encyclopedia of Australian Science)
This school ceased to exist when the Northern Territory University became part of the new Charles Darwin University in 2004.

items.definition: The University of Adelaide is a university in Adelaide, South Australia, which was established in 1874. Its main campus is on North Terrace in the Adelaide city centre. The university has three other campuses throughout the state: Roseworthy; Waite; and Thebarton; and the Ngee Ann–Adelaide Education Centre (NAAEC), in Singapore.

The School of Biological Sciences was formed in 2015, and brings together parts of the former schools of Earth and Environmental Sciences (EES), and Molecular and Biomedical Sciences (MBS). The School of Biological Sciences was formed to coordinate and consolidate the University's research and teaching in Ecology and Environmental Science; Genetics and Evolution; and Molecular and Cellular Biology.

prefLabel._value: School of Biological Sciences, The University of Adelaide

items.definition: The University of Canberra was first established in 1967 as the Canberra College of Advanced Education. The Canberra CAE became the University of Canberra under sponsorship of Monash University in 1990. The University is located in Bruce, Canberra. (Courtesy of wikipedia)

The Institute for Applied Ecology's core purpose is to undertake high quality research which improves our understanding of the environment to enhance decision-making for natural resource management and sustainable development. The Institute undertakes broadly based environmental research across four interrelated science programs: Conservation Ecology, Water Science, Ecochemistry and Toxicology, and Environmental Genetics and Genomics.
